{"lemma":"ثَرِيدِ","slug":"ثَرِيدِ","root":"ث.ر.د","root_slug":"ث-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4388"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tharid (Arab dish of bread in broth)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"porridge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alcoholic beverages' foams"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thread such as one in a forum or microblogging service"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thread such as in a CPU"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Persian ترید (tarid, “a soup”), apparently in a variant as ثَلْجَم (ṯaljam), and possibly ultimately from a diminutive of Ancient Greek ἴτριον (ítrion), hence doublet of إِطْرِيَة (ʔiṭriya).\n\nFrom English thread."},"ipa":["/θa.riːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4388","headword_ar":"ثَرِيدٌ","root":"vrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavoruwdN","text_ar":"مَثْرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"Bread"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken into small pieces, with the fingers, and then moistened with broth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken"},{"kind":"text","text":"bread. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also, the former, (T, A,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variydapN","text_ar":"ثَرِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vurodapN","text_ar":"ثُرْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varuwdapN","text_ar":"ثَرُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavoruwdapN","text_ar":"مَثْرُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K accord. to the TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uvorudaAnN","text_ar":"اُثْرُدَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, M, * K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken into small pieces, with the fingers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, * M, A, Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then moistened with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, Msb) &c., (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then piled up in the middle of a bowl;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally having some flesh-meat with it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variydapN","text_ar":"ثَرِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":335},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variyd","text_ar":"ثَرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bread crumbled"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (T;) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varuwdapN","text_ar":"ثَرُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavoruwdapN","text_ar":"مَثْرُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":] that of Ghassán is said by common consent to have been"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared with marrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with eggs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the yolks of eggs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and there was no kind more delicious than these two kinds. (TA.) The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrydp","text_ar":"ثريدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varaAy^idu","text_ar":"ثَرَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vurudN","text_ar":"ثُرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vurodN","text_ar":"ثُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, and Ham p. 524;) the last of which is a contraction of that next preceding it. (Ham ubi suprà.) A poet, as cited by IAar, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      A^alaA yaA xubozu yaA A@bonapa yavorudaAnK\n                      \n                     \n                        A^abaY AlHuloquwmu baEodaki laA yanaAmu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now surely, O bread, O daughter of two preparers of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variyd","text_ar":"ثَرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the throat refuses, after"},{"kind":"text","text":"swallowing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thee, to rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of desire for more]: he says that the poet calls the bread after two young men, or slaves, who were preparing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vryd","text_ar":"ثريد"},{"kind":"text","text":", and gives tenween to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yvrdAn","text_ar":"يثردان"},{"kind":"text","text":"by a poetic license, instead of saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yavorudaAni","text_ar":"يَثْرُدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, as it is [originally] a verbal phrase, he should have said by rule: but the word, as Fr relates it, is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uvorudaAnK","text_ar":"اُثْرُدَانٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and [ISd says,] I think that this is a determinate subst., for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~ariyd","text_ar":"الثَّرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almavoruwd","text_ar":"المَثْرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore properly imperfectly decl., but here made perfectly decl. by a poetic license. (M.) It is said in a trad. that the excellence of 'Áïsheh above other women is as the excellence of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vryd","text_ar":"ثريد"},{"kind":"text","text":"above other kinds of food; but it is said that what is here meant is food prepared with flesh-meat, together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vryd","text_ar":"ثريد"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is generally prepared with flesh-meat, and it is said to be one of the two things called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHom","text_ar":"لَحْم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","T","A","M","K","S","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}